  "articleSummary": "This tutorial uses a custom `delay(millisecs)` function and animated timelines to visualize how JavaScript Promises execute. It demonstrates correct usage (passing a function reference to `.then`), a common mistake (invoking `console.log` immediately instead of passing it), simultaneous independent Promises, and `Promise.all` waiting for all to resolve. The tone is educational with a focus on visual learning, targeting developers who want to avoid typical Promise pitfalls.",
